      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIDNITE MUSCLE (9) turned in an uncharacteristically poor run last start when 6 metres away in fifth over 1690m at Kilmore. Finds a nice race and can improve sharply. BLACKRANGE GLORY (10) broke in the run and finished seventh, beaten 24 metres, first-up last time out over 2100m at Charlton. Hard to know where he gets from this slightly awkward draw. Meets a similar line up so he is sure to be a force if the manners improve. THE CHOOK (7) is better than her last-start run for seventh over 2150m at Bendigo would suggest. Worth another chance. AI SEDHAI (1) must be considered after she finished runner-up over 1690m at this track two-and-a-half weeks ago after she raced outside the leader at the bell.",
